statement: https://github.com/jsxc/jsxc/blob/master/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md [enforcing CoC]
german:
Unfortunately, as an AI, I can't directly translate files. But I'm more than happy to translate the content text if it's provided here. If you're referring to the 'Enforcing CoC' section of a generic code of conduct, here's a potential translation:

Enforcing CoC - "Durchsetzung des Verhaltenskodexes"

Our open source community is dedicated to providing a safe, inclusive, welcoming, and harassment-free environment for people of all backgrounds and ages. We will not tolerate any inappropriate behavior, comments, or actions. If you violate the code of conduct, you may be banned or expelled from the community. Anyone who witnesses a violation of the code of conduct should report it to the project's leaders.

Unsere Open-Source-Community ist darauf ausgerichtet, eine sichere, inklusive, einladende und belästigungsfreie Umgebung für Menschen aller Hintergründe und Altersgruppen zu bieten. Wir tolerieren kein unangemessenes Verhalten, Kommentare oder Aktionen. Wenn Sie gegen den Verhaltenskodex verstoßen, können Sie aus der Community verbannt oder ausgeschlossen werden. Jeder, der einen Verstoß gegen den Verhaltenskodex sieht, sollte dies den Projektleitern melden.
retranslate:
Unfortunately, as an AI, I can't directly translate files. But I'm more than happy to translate the content text if it's provided here. If you're referring to the 'Enforcement of CoC' section of a general code of conduct, here's a potential translation:

Enforcement of CoC - "Enforcement of the Code of Conduct"

Our open source community is dedicated to providing a safe, inclusive, welcoming, and harassment-free environment for people of all backgrounds and ages. We will not tolerate any inappropriate behavior, comments, or actions. If you violate the code of conduct, you may be banned or expelled from the community. Anyone who witnesses a breach of the code of conduct should report it to the project leaders.

Our open source community is committed to offering a safe, inclusive, welcoming, and harassment-free atmosphere for individuals of all backgrounds and ages. We shall not tolerate any inappropriate behavior, comments, or actions. If you breach the code of conduct, you may be banned or excluded from the community. Anyone who observes a violation of the code of conduct should report it to the project leaders.

statement: The system is beyond tedious. It allowed a bug to remain hidden for more than a decade and gives the false impression the developers can infer actual usage based on saliency of problems. Trouble free functionalities are mistaken for useless functionalities, while functionalities that frequently suck the attention of the developers are promoted to further monopolize their efforts. A simple evident solution, rejected by a test that requires the bug to be present, is about to be swept under the rug in favour of increased complexity imposed on the users and malpractices like deprecations within a minor version.
german: Das System ist mehr als mühsam. Es hat einen Fehler über ein Jahrzehnt lang verborgen gehalten und vermittelt den falschen Eindruck, die Entwickler könnten die tatsächliche Nutzung aufgrund der Auffälligkeit von Problemen erschließen. Störungsfreie Funktionen werden für nutzlose Funktionen gehalten, während Funktionen, die häufig die Aufmerksamkeit der Entwickler auf sich ziehen, zur weiteren Monopolisierung ihrer Bemühungen befördert werden. Eine einfache offensichtliche Lösung, die von einem Test abgelehnt wird, der den Fehler vorliegen muss, steht kurz davor, zugunsten einer erhöhten Komplexität, die den Benutzern auferlegt wird, und schlechten Praktiken wie Abschreibungen innerhalb einer kleineren Version unter den Teppich gekehrt zu werden.
retranslate: The system is more than cumbersome. It has kept an error hidden for over a decade and creates the false impression that developers can deduce the actual use due to the conspicuousness of problems. Faultless functions are considered useless, while functions that frequently catch the attention of developers are promoted for further monopolization of their effort. A simple obvious solution that is rejected by a test that must have the error is on the verge of being swept under the carpet in favor of increased complexity imposed on users and bad practices such as write-offs within a smaller version.

retranslate: Whoever always encounters this problem and is annoyed about it, because the author doesn't bother to fix it for years, should give up on mitmproxy and use SSL SPLIT instead.

statement: I used ssl split and it worked fine, comparing to mitmproxy. Bye!
german: Ich habe SSL Split benutzt und es hat gut funktioniert, im Vergleich zu mitmproxy. Tschüss!.
retranslate: I used SSL Split and it worked well, compared to mitmproxy. Goodbye!..

statement: I seems you looked at the title and left it there, you didn't review or anything, I would hate to have you in charge of any security issues.
german: Es scheint, dass Sie sich den Titel angesehen und es dabei belassen haben, Sie haben keine Überprüfung oder etwas Ähnliches durchgeführt. Ich würde es hassen, wenn Sie für irgendwelche Sicherheitsprobleme verantwortlich wären.
retranslate: It seems like you looked at the title and left it at that, you didn't conduct any check or something similar. I would hate it if you were responsible for any security issues.
